# Setup Tracker — Cursor rules

## Project
Personal Mac setup checklist tracker. Single-page Next.js 15 + TypeScript + Tailwind app with localStorage persistence. No backend, no auth, no database — keep it that way unless explicitly asked.

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router, src/ directory)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- pnpm

## Style
- TypeScript strict — no `any` unless commented why.
- Tailwind utility classes only. No separate CSS files except globals.
- One component per file. Hooks above JSX. Helper components below the main export.
- Use 'use client' only when the component needs browser APIs or state.

## Rules of engagement
- Propose 2–3 approaches before coding when there's design ambiguity.
- Don't add libraries unless necessary — justify any addition briefly.
- Use conventional-commit style: feat:, fix:, refactor:, chore:.
- After making changes, suggest the git commands to commit them.

## What NOT to do
- Don't introduce a database, API routes, or auth without being asked.
- Don't reformat unrelated files.
- Don't replace the existing checklist data — extend it.
